Select tag: 
	In HTML, the <select> tag is used to create a dropdown list.
	The choices inside it are defined using <option> tags.
	
Select class in Selenium :
	In Selenium, the Select class is used to handle dropdown elements created using the HTML <select> tag.
	Selenium cannot directly select dropdown options like normal elements, so it provides the Select class
	to handle them easily.
	
Steps to Use Select Class : 
	Locate the dropdown element.
	Create a Select object.
	Select option using available methods.
	
Some important methods:
| Method                  | Description                          |
| ----------------------- | ------------------------------------ |
|  selectByVisibleText()  | Select using displayed text          |
|  selectByValue()        | Select using value attribute         |
|  selectByIndex()        | Select using option index            |
|  getOptions()           | Get all dropdown options             |
|  isMultiple()           | Check if multiple selection allowed  |
|  deselectAll()          | Deselect options (multi-select only) |
